WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.979 --> 00:00:16.979
<i>Ripped. corrected and synced by:
Yoav1610</i>

2
00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:19.080
Did you know what your husband did
on October 7th?

3
00:00:19.160 --> 00:00:21.200
I know my husband.
I know who he is.

4
00:00:21.360 --> 00:00:23.040
I know how wonderful he is.

5
00:00:26.320 --> 00:00:29.520
Maher's murder shook me so deeply

6
00:00:29.600 --> 00:00:30.920
that I decided to come here.

7
00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:32.480
And now that I'm so close to the goal.

8
00:00:32.560 --> 00:00:36.240
I'm just afraid I'll do something
I won't be able to live with.

9
00:00:37.120 --> 00:00:40.320
Have you ever killed?
-Yes. I have.

10
00:00:42.600 --> 00:00:45.640
Anne. wait a moment. please.

11
00:00:46.800 --> 00:00:49.080
It's possible the source of the pain
is not physical.

12
00:00:49.360 --> 00:00:51.160
Your body is able
to hold the shrapnel.

13
00:00:51.520 --> 00:00:53.600
the question is what you're holding onto.

14
00:00:53.760 --> 00:00:57.320
Today we go into a heroic
operation

15
00:00:57.400 --> 00:01:00.240
and our names will remain engraved
in the pages of history.

16
00:01:00.320 --> 00:01:02.320
To activate it.
you have to press the switch.

17
00:01:02.640 --> 00:01:03.560
Speak. I'm listening.

18
00:01:03.840 --> 00:01:04.800
Listen to me carefully.

19
00:01:05.040 --> 00:01:07.520
five vehicles are leaving Tubas.
from the "Al-Quds" school.

20
00:01:07.680 --> 00:01:08.960
Four terrorists in each vehicle.

21
00:01:09.120 --> 00:01:09.920
Open fire!

22
00:01:17.120 --> 00:01:18.560
Copy. I identify one body in the vehicle.

23
00:01:19.160 --> 00:01:20.400
The vehicle looks clean.

24
00:01:20.560 --> 00:01:22.480
The vehicle is clean.
I repeat. the vehicle is clean.

25
00:01:22.720 --> 00:01:23.880
What the hell is going on here?

26
00:01:24.080 --> 00:01:25.680
Is your gun loaded?
-Yes.

27
00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:29.520
It's time.
Switch to active mode... now.

28
00:01:33.440 --> 00:01:34.520
Get out of the car!

29
00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:36.840
Don't do anything.
give that to me.

30
00:01:37.280 --> 00:01:38.720
They're on their way to the Wall.
We have to stop them.

31
00:01:38.920 --> 00:01:40.000
It was a diversion.

32
00:01:40.480 --> 00:01:42.240
He played you. Doron.
He played all of us.

33
00:02:12.080 --> 00:02:12.880
Thank you.

34
00:04:01.400 --> 00:04:02.600
After Eli died.

35
00:04:04.360 --> 00:04:08.000
they took me to some village
and I was there in some room.

36
00:04:08.200 --> 00:04:09.000
they tied me up.

37
00:04:16.560 --> 00:04:18.760
And I had time to think.

38
00:04:22.240 --> 00:04:25.360
And suddenly everything fell into place.
It happened.

39
00:04:26.880 --> 00:04:27.760
What?

40
00:04:28.920 --> 00:04:30.240
I remembered everything.

41
00:04:30.640 --> 00:04:33.360
All the hours that had gone missing for me.

42
00:04:34.880 --> 00:04:36.320
It was like all the pieces connected.

43
00:04:43.360 --> 00:04:44.560
The phone from Eli.

44
00:04:46.280 --> 00:04:47.360
the trip.

45
00:04:49.920 --> 00:04:51.000
the party.

46
00:04:54.600 --> 00:04:56.240
the girl I couldn't save.

47
00:05:03.240 --> 00:05:04.640
Hagit's house.

48
00:05:16.080 --> 00:05:17.240
And then I understood.

49
00:05:19.920 --> 00:05:21.800
Eli died two years ago already.

50
00:05:25.600 --> 00:05:27.520
Now he's only leaving us
physically.

51
00:05:31.000 --> 00:05:32.320
I let him go.

52
00:05:45.320 --> 00:05:50.160
You have to help me understand something
because it just doesn't add up.

53
00:05:50.280 --> 00:05:53.240
I have to understand what makes
someone like you.

54
00:05:53.680 --> 00:05:57.080
a French woman from the upper-middle
class. Catholic.

55
00:05:57.160 --> 00:06:01.440
carry out a suicide bombing in Israel.

56
00:06:04.720 --> 00:06:06.440
After my husband died. I...

57
00:06:06.840 --> 00:06:10.160
I've heard enough about your husband.

58
00:06:11.320 --> 00:06:12.760
I'm talking about you.

59
00:06:12.840 --> 00:06:16.840
Anne Zaytoun. the little blonde
who wakes up in the morning

60
00:06:16.920 --> 00:06:20.120
and straps ten kilos
of explosives onto herself.

61
00:06:20.520 --> 00:06:24.840
and plans to murder innocent
Israelis. civilians.

62
00:06:24.920 --> 00:06:28.400
My mission was to kill
your agent. Amir...

63
00:06:28.880 --> 00:06:30.800
I mean. whatever his name is...

64
00:06:31.280 --> 00:06:32.920
and he is not innocent.

65
00:06:33.880 --> 00:06:36.320
And your friends.
what exactly are they planning to do?

66
00:06:36.520 --> 00:06:38.200
I don't know.

67
00:06:38.600 --> 00:06:41.480
You know very well
that they're on their way to Israel

68
00:06:41.560 --> 00:06:43.720
to carry out this attack.

69
00:06:44.160 --> 00:06:47.160
Doesn't that seem a little twisted to you?

70
00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:51.040
There are no uninvolved people
in a conflict like this.

71
00:06:51.120 --> 00:06:53.000
You said that about the Palestinians.

72
00:06:53.720 --> 00:06:58.120
Why are you always surprised
when it's turned on your side?

73
00:06:58.760 --> 00:07:00.600
Where does this sense of justice of yours come from?

74
00:07:00.680 --> 00:07:01.880
Great.

75
00:07:02.080 --> 00:07:03.240
So you agree.

76
00:07:03.320 --> 00:07:05.920
I didn't say that. I'm only saying
that you do the same things.

77
00:07:06.080 --> 00:07:09.600
and no. I'm not in favor
of killing innocents.

78
00:07:09.680 --> 00:07:12.320
on either side.

79
00:07:12.480 --> 00:07:13.960
So prove it.

80
00:07:14.360 --> 00:07:16.480
because very soon...

81
00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:18.680
women

82
00:07:19.000 --> 00:07:20.400
and children

83
00:07:20.920 --> 00:07:24.280
who did nothing to anyone

84
00:07:24.720 --> 00:07:28.800
will be slaughtered while they scream and cry.

85
00:07:29.120 --> 00:07:30.680
You have the ability to prevent it.

86
00:07:31.960 --> 00:07:34.960
If your friends succeed
in this attack.

87
00:07:37.280 --> 00:07:39.680
you'll be in prison until the day you die.

88
00:07:41.080 --> 00:07:45.240
No one will save you. Hamas
won't make a deal to free you.

89
00:07:45.720 --> 00:07:47.600
You're nothing to them.

90
00:07:48.640 --> 00:07:50.440
You have an ace up your sleeve.

91
00:07:51.160 --> 00:07:52.920
Use it now.

92
00:07:54.000 --> 00:07:55.200
What's the plan?

93
00:07:56.640 --> 00:07:57.800
Where will it happen?

94
00:07:58.640 --> 00:08:00.560
I don't know.

95
00:08:53.640 --> 00:08:54.920
It's Gabi.

96
00:08:56.320 --> 00:08:58.640
So. Gabi? Is she talking?
-They knew everything.

97
00:08:59.680 --> 00:09:02.280
What is everything?
-Her mission was to kill you.

98
00:09:02.360 --> 00:09:04.080
She knows you're connected
to her husband's assassination.

99
00:09:05.160 --> 00:09:06.960
How does she know?
-Doron. they're not stupid.

100
00:09:07.080 --> 00:09:08.600
After Eli was caught. they figured it all out.

101
00:09:09.000 --> 00:09:10.360
She doesn't exactly know
who pulled the trigger.

102
00:09:10.520 --> 00:09:12.640
but as far as she's concerned.
anyone who was in the area is a dead man.

103
00:09:13.320 --> 00:09:14.520
Let's get things straight for a moment.

104
00:09:14.760 --> 00:09:17.720
Before Eli was exposed.
you two were involved. right?

105
00:09:18.040 --> 00:09:19.120
More or less.

106
00:09:20.360 --> 00:09:22.320
That means their original plan
was the Wall.

107
00:09:22.600 --> 00:09:24.360
That fits the plans
we trained on at the camp.

108
00:09:24.440 --> 00:09:26.960
but Said probably
changed the target now. -Apparently.

109
00:09:27.480 --> 00:09:29.640
Either way.
at the Wall we're secured to the max.

110
00:09:29.720 --> 00:09:31.240
We're covered there completely.

111
00:09:32.120 --> 00:09:33.720
Do you really think
Anne doesn't know anything?

112
00:09:35.080 --> 00:09:37.520
I have no idea. I can't
figure out these Europeans.

113
00:09:38.040 --> 00:09:40.880
Bring me a Palestinian. one look
and I know guilty or not guilty.

114
00:09:41.160 --> 00:09:44.640
And what is she even doing here anyway?
-Revenge. She told you. didn't she?

115
00:09:45.440 --> 00:09:46.840
Does she even realize what her husband did?

116
00:09:49.000 --> 00:09:51.240
More or less.
-What do you mean. more or less?

117
00:09:51.800 --> 00:09:54.400
She doesn't know what her husband did?
-He definitely didn't tell her.

118
00:09:56.000 --> 00:09:58.960
Okay. Doron. get to the facility.
I need you here.

119
00:10:00.400 --> 00:10:01.360
Okay.

120
00:10:09.360 --> 00:10:10.400
I have to go.

121
00:10:12.280 --> 00:10:13.400
So it's not over yet?

122
00:10:25.480 --> 00:10:26.280
Bye.

123
00:10:35.240 --> 00:10:39.280
Yes? -Dana. I need
you to get me something urgent. -What?

124
00:10:39.760 --> 00:10:42.600
Maher's recorded testimony.
-Okay. no problem.

125
00:10:42.720 --> 00:10:43.960
I'll text the archive now.

126
00:10:44.280 --> 00:10:45.960
What about the French woman? Did she start singing?

127
00:10:46.280 --> 00:10:48.440
She'll be singing in six languages soon.
don't worry.

128
00:10:48.880 --> 00:10:51.600
Get it to me
as fast as possible. -Okay.

129
00:10:55.120 --> 00:10:57.240
Anything new?
-Not yet.

130
00:11:02.440 --> 00:11:04.800
I honestly don't know
what came over me.

131
00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:10.000
Maybe I thought
that if I recruited Maher

132
00:11:10.120 --> 00:11:13.760
I'd somehow be able to make up
for... -Make up for what?

133
00:11:15.960 --> 00:11:17.200
For our failure.

134
00:11:19.640 --> 00:11:21.200
For how they lulled us to sleep like that.

135
00:11:24.000 --> 00:11:25.040
It won't leave me alone.

136
00:11:26.120 --> 00:11:28.240
More than anyone.
I should have seen it coming.

137
00:11:29.040 --> 00:11:31.720
Dana. an entire country
didn't see it coming.

138
00:11:32.080 --> 00:11:33.200
An entire country isn't me.

139
00:11:34.720 --> 00:11:35.680
It isn't us.

140
00:11:38.720 --> 00:11:40.400
We just got screwed.

141
00:11:42.680 --> 00:11:45.720
Tell me. do you think you're the only one
walking around with all this crap

142
00:11:45.840 --> 00:11:46.800
of failure and guilt?

143
00:11:48.240 --> 00:11:49.680
Everyone here walks around with it.

144
00:11:49.760 --> 00:11:52.240
it's part of the air.
it's part of our breathing ever since.

145
00:11:54.360 --> 00:11:56.320
Self-pity
isn't a work plan.

146
00:11:58.560 --> 00:12:01.880
You have to put all of it aside
and focus on the here and now.

147
00:12:04.360 --> 00:12:06.920
The here and now.
-Exactly.

148
00:12:08.320 --> 00:12:10.040
You know. I don't think
I can. Naama.

149
00:12:13.920 --> 00:12:15.560
What kind of person recruits the man

150
00:12:15.640 --> 00:12:17.600
who murdered the family
of his friend. huh?

151
00:12:20.680 --> 00:12:21.840
What a mistake.

152
00:12:23.360 --> 00:12:26.200
I should have stopped trying
to prove to the world how worthy I am.

153
00:12:27.880 --> 00:12:31.160
All because of guilt
and a few pieces of shrapnel in my skull.

154
00:12:36.560 --> 00:12:37.560
Are you done?

155
00:12:40.480 --> 00:12:41.680
I trust you.

156
00:12:43.040 --> 00:12:44.800
I trusted you when you recruited Maher.

157
00:12:44.920 --> 00:12:47.320
I trusted you when you recruited
those three lunatics.

158
00:12:49.120 --> 00:12:51.440
and even when you lied to me
about Maher's death.

159
00:12:54.880 --> 00:12:57.480
You knew about that?
-What do you think?

160
00:12:58.360 --> 00:13:01.240
That I sit in this chair because of
my pretty. sad eyes?

161
00:13:03.880 --> 00:13:05.320
Dana. I know everything.

162
00:13:06.640 --> 00:13:07.880
That's my job.

163
00:13:08.680 --> 00:13:12.880
and when an employee of mine lies
I smell it from a kilometer away.

164
00:13:15.000 --> 00:13:16.080
Why didn't you tell me?

165
00:13:18.320 --> 00:13:21.760
Because officially I can't exactly
cooperate with something like that.

166
00:13:23.560 --> 00:13:25.600
But believe me.
if I were in your place.

167
00:13:25.800 --> 00:13:27.320
that's exactly what I would have done.

168
00:13:29.160 --> 00:13:32.800
You wanted to save lives.
Nothing else matters.

169
00:13:34.600 --> 00:13:35.880
Now pull yourself together

170
00:13:36.320 --> 00:13:38.240
because while you're sinking
into self-pity

171
00:13:38.320 --> 00:13:40.520
there's enough crap out there to deal with.

172
00:13:42.560 --> 00:13:43.600
Is there?

173
00:13:45.720 --> 00:13:46.640
There is.

174
00:14:02.720 --> 00:14:05.160
What's happening?
-What's the situation?

175
00:14:15.000 --> 00:14:16.560
How did he slip away from us like that. huh?

176
00:14:21.520 --> 00:14:22.720
What? Say something.

177
00:14:24.280 --> 00:14:25.360
What is there to say?

178
00:14:27.360 --> 00:14:29.880
What? What was there?
What... how did it happen?

179
00:14:30.760 --> 00:14:32.000
The incident isn't over yet. brother.

180
00:14:32.440 --> 00:14:34.120
When it's over we'll sit. talk about everything.

181
00:14:35.120 --> 00:14:37.760
Okay? -Solid. yeah.

182
00:14:38.960 --> 00:14:40.240
How was prison?

183
00:14:43.280 --> 00:14:46.560
Forget it. never mind. It... it was.

184
00:14:50.000 --> 00:14:51.280
Are we good?

185
00:14:53.240 --> 00:14:54.200
Why. what?

186
00:14:54.880 --> 00:14:56.080
I don't know. everything that happened.

187
00:14:59.320 --> 00:15:00.280
What happened?

188
00:15:11.400 --> 00:15:12.240
Everything's fine.

189
00:15:28.520 --> 00:15:30.840
Everything okay? Did you check it?
-Everything's ready.

190
00:15:36.720 --> 00:15:38.040
We have no news from Anne.

191
00:15:41.160 --> 00:15:42.360
I know.

192
00:15:43.360 --> 00:15:45.440
Do you think the Israelis caught her?

193
00:15:47.920 --> 00:15:50.680
That's a possibility we prepared for.

194
00:15:51.160 --> 00:15:53.120
Her mission was to kill
the traitor.

195
00:15:54.080 --> 00:15:56.320
we knew we were taking a risk.

196
00:15:56.840 --> 00:15:58.200
And if she talks?

197
00:16:01.760 --> 00:16:03.480
I trust her.

198
00:16:04.840 --> 00:16:07.040
Anne has already proven herself.

199
00:16:08.480 --> 00:16:11.480
Even if she didn't succeed in the mission.

200
00:16:12.120 --> 00:16:15.520
I'm sure she'll stay loyal
to the cause. -I hope so.

201
00:16:18.360 --> 00:16:19.800
Go to sleep.

202
00:16:20.440 --> 00:16:22.400
tomorrow we have a whole day ahead of us.

203
00:16:29.960 --> 00:16:32.520
Said. you can't come with us.

204
00:16:32.880 --> 00:16:34.800
It's dangerous. you're too important.

205
00:16:45.120 --> 00:16:46.520
I want to come there.

206
00:16:48.160 --> 00:16:51.760
I want to take part in our victory.
do you understand?

207
00:16:55.000 --> 00:16:59.240
Are you sure?
-Go to sleep. -Okay.

208
00:17:07.560 --> 00:17:09.960
Tell me what you did on October 7th.

209
00:17:11.240 --> 00:17:15.000
I was a company commander in the central camps.

210
00:17:15.400 --> 00:17:17.840
Our objective was
to raid the nearby kibbutz.

211
00:17:18.480 --> 00:17:24.200
Me and a few guys who were with me
killed the guard who stood at the gate.

212
00:17:24.480 --> 00:17:26.880
then we moved between the houses

213
00:17:27.560 --> 00:17:29.720
and took captive everyone
we could take.

214
00:17:30.520 --> 00:17:32.200
And what happened to those
you couldn't take?

215
00:17:32.280 --> 00:17:33.760
We killed them.

216
00:17:35.920 --> 00:17:39.080
How many did you kill there? How many in total?

217
00:17:39.760 --> 00:17:41.520
I don't remember exactly.

218
00:17:42.720 --> 00:17:44.720
I think. about 20.

219
00:17:45.240 --> 00:17:47.680
We took some with us and some died on the way.

220
00:17:48.120 --> 00:17:50.320
How many people did you kill yourself?

221
00:17:50.400 --> 00:17:52.560
Soldiers or civilians?

222
00:17:52.800 --> 00:17:57.080
Let's talk first about the children.
the babies and the women.

223
00:17:58.800 --> 00:17:59.840
Five.

224
00:18:00.880 --> 00:18:02.200
Tell me about them.

225
00:18:03.720 --> 00:18:07.840
In the first house. the man came out with a knife
so I had to shoot him.

226
00:18:16.080 --> 00:18:19.080
In the fourth house. I think.
I killed the eldest son.

227
00:18:19.160 --> 00:18:20.600
He tried to run away. so...

228
00:18:21.080 --> 00:18:22.520
I had to shoot him.

229
00:18:24.600 --> 00:18:26.360
How old was he?

230
00:18:27.560 --> 00:18:31.440
14. 15.
-Okay. good. go on.

231
00:18:33.440 --> 00:18:39.120
The last house belonged to a soldier.
but he wasn't home.

232
00:18:39.560 --> 00:18:43.680
The woman and children hid in the safe room.

233
00:18:44.280 --> 00:18:47.600
and there was a Bedouin with them who worked for them.

234
00:18:49.360 --> 00:18:52.640
We tried to convince them to open
the door but they refused.

235
00:18:53.440 --> 00:18:56.200
so we had to break down the door.

236
00:18:57.200 --> 00:18:59.440
The woman fled with the children through the window.

237
00:18:59.520 --> 00:19:01.760
We caught them and brought them back home.

238
00:19:03.640 --> 00:19:08.600
She even tried to fight
and stabbed one of the guys who was with me.

239
00:19:10.000 --> 00:19:11.400
Go on.

240
00:19:12.600 --> 00:19:15.080
One of the guys murdered the children.

241
00:19:17.520 --> 00:19:20.080
And you. what did you do?

242
00:19:21.640 --> 00:19:24.360
I took the woman to a room...

243
00:19:27.000 --> 00:19:29.520
Well. and what did you do to her there?

244
00:19:33.720 --> 00:19:35.120
I touched her.

245
00:19:38.240 --> 00:19:41.320
Did you only touch her or also sleep with her?

246
00:19:51.000 --> 00:19:54.560
You mean. you raped the woman. right?

247
00:19:55.840 --> 00:19:57.640
You dog. you bastard.

248
00:19:59.360 --> 00:20:01.840
And what did you do to her afterward. you lowlife?

249
00:20:04.120 --> 00:20:05.320
I killed her.

250
00:20:15.200 --> 00:20:16.560
Drink.

251
00:20:25.600 --> 00:20:27.760
This is about Ali's wife.

252
00:20:28.400 --> 00:20:30.320
His real name was Eli.

253
00:20:32.280 --> 00:20:34.040
Her name is Hagit.

254
00:20:38.200 --> 00:20:40.760
I know there's no chance
you support this.

255
00:20:44.520 --> 00:20:47.280
So. Anne. I'm asking you.
I'm begging you.

256
00:20:47.360 --> 00:20:49.840
if you have any information

257
00:20:50.600 --> 00:20:52.000
that can help us

258
00:20:52.600 --> 00:20:56.680
prevent this terrible plan
of Said's. please. talk.

259
00:20:59.120 --> 00:21:00.560
Please.

260
00:21:12.480 --> 00:21:16.040
When... when we fled the camp

261
00:21:16.200 --> 00:21:18.760
we were in some village...

262
00:21:19.160 --> 00:21:23.080
and Said was working on plans...

263
00:21:23.440 --> 00:21:25.600
and I saw pictures of it.

264
00:21:26.480 --> 00:21:29.120
Pictures of what?
-A cemetery.

265
00:21:32.400 --> 00:21:33.760
What cemetery?

266
00:21:34.080 --> 00:21:36.200
Said talked about...

267
00:21:36.640 --> 00:21:40.280
this day of yours.
where you remember the dead.

268
00:21:41.240 --> 00:21:44.640
When you... when you stand
to honor them...

269
00:21:45.280 --> 00:21:48.000
And he talked about it with envy.

270
00:21:50.040 --> 00:21:55.680
He said the Jews honor them
as if they're still alive.

271
00:22:06.640 --> 00:22:07.680
Thank you.

272
00:22:15.360 --> 00:22:16.320
Well?

273
00:22:17.680 --> 00:22:19.280
They're going for Memorial Day.

274
00:22:41.000 --> 00:22:43.520
In a few hours hundreds of thousands of citizens
are expected

275
00:22:43.840 --> 00:22:45.520
to visit the military cemeteries

276
00:22:45.720 --> 00:22:48.280
and the dozens of military plots
across the country.

277
00:22:49.520 --> 00:22:53.720
Children. elderly. families and individuals.
all will come to pay respects

278
00:22:53.800 --> 00:22:55.840
to those who sacrificed their lives for us.

279
00:22:57.080 --> 00:22:58.920
As of now we have an immediate alert

280
00:22:59.000 --> 00:23:00.920
of an intention to carry out an attack today

281
00:23:01.120 --> 00:23:02.360
at one of these targets.

282
00:23:02.880 --> 00:23:06.160
The working assumption is that the attackers
have marked the main targets.

283
00:23:06.760 --> 00:23:09.080
However. no risks are being taken

284
00:23:09.160 --> 00:23:12.440
and forces are on full alert
at each of the cemeteries.

285
00:23:12.720 --> 00:23:15.160
Anyone holding a weapon
is outside.

286
00:23:15.680 --> 00:23:17.560
True. we don't have a focused alert.

287
00:23:17.840 --> 00:23:19.640
but we can't
cancel the ceremonies.

288
00:23:20.560 --> 00:23:23.400
Closing the cemeteries and cancelling the ceremonies
is surrender.

289
00:23:23.880 --> 00:23:25.600
This day is sacred to all of us.

290
00:23:26.640 --> 00:23:29.680
and our enemies understand that
and will try to desecrate it.

291
00:23:30.240 --> 00:23:32.760
We won't let that happen.

292
00:23:33.720 --> 00:23:34.560
To work.

293
00:23:35.800 --> 00:23:38.800
Nesher to Be'er Sheva command post.
Sniper force deployed.

294
00:23:43.280 --> 00:23:45.560
Okay. Passing it to her.

295
00:23:49.800 --> 00:23:52.360
Naama. I don't know how
relevant this is

296
00:23:52.560 --> 00:23:54.840
but we got a call
from a taxi station manager in Jerusalem.

297
00:23:55.120 --> 00:23:58.120
Go on. -About an hour ago
two Europeans came to the station.

298
00:23:58.360 --> 00:24:00.120
tourists who seemed suspicious to him.

299
00:24:00.280 --> 00:24:02.880
They ordered a ride to the Kiryat Shaul
cemetery in Tel Aviv.

300
00:24:03.520 --> 00:24:06.040
A few minutes later four more arrived
matching the same profile

301
00:24:06.240 --> 00:24:08.000
and ordered a ride to the cemetery
in Hod HaSharon

302
00:24:08.080 --> 00:24:09.640
and to the cemetery in Holon.

303
00:24:09.840 --> 00:24:13.080
He tried to talk to them.
to understand what they were looking for there.

304
00:24:13.240 --> 00:24:14.080
but they were evasive.

305
00:24:14.280 --> 00:24:16.440
and some of the drivers already reported
dropping off the passengers.

306
00:24:17.080 --> 00:24:18.160
It's them. Naama.

307
00:24:19.160 --> 00:24:20.280
It's them. Give me a second.

308
00:24:20.520 --> 00:24:21.600
This is an indication.

309
00:24:21.840 --> 00:24:23.160
They made a mistake leaving from the same station.

310
00:24:24.880 --> 00:24:27.240
Let's run an immediate survey
on taxis from Jerusalem.

311
00:24:27.400 --> 00:24:28.440
we'll look for more targets.

312
00:24:28.640 --> 00:24:30.560
We have to update the field commanders quickly

313
00:24:30.680 --> 00:24:32.440
at Kiryat Shaul. Hod HaSharon and Holon.

314
00:24:32.600 --> 00:24:34.480
And reinforce the forces
at those cemeteries.

315
00:24:44.160 --> 00:24:46.640
They left Jerusalem an hour and a half ago.
They're probably already with you.

316
00:24:46.840 --> 00:24:48.960
Gabi. is this certain? Is it them?
-Yes.

317
00:24:49.200 --> 00:24:52.240
We estimate there are several terrorist
cells on their way to other targets.

318
00:24:52.480 --> 00:24:54.360
We're sending reinforcements
to the cemeteries in the center.

319
00:24:54.480 --> 00:24:55.400
It's too late to evacuate.

320
00:24:55.760 --> 00:24:57.560
They might already be inside.
-Copy.

321
00:24:58.840 --> 00:25:01.800
Gordon stations. copy.
we have high suspicion they're already here.

322
00:25:02.520 --> 00:25:03.480
Keep your eyes open.

323
00:25:46.440 --> 00:25:47.560
Good thing you're here.

324
00:25:59.880 --> 00:26:01.440
Okay. what? Are we standing here
like potted plants? What?

325
00:26:02.240 --> 00:26:04.520
Let's split up. We'll go inside.

326
00:26:05.000 --> 00:26:07.240
Go to the graves over there. I'll take the inner
parking lot.

327
00:26:08.040 --> 00:26:09.280
Look for Europeans in their 30s.

328
00:26:09.960 --> 00:26:11.600
Okay. Come on.

329
00:26:27.480 --> 00:26:28.680
Continue from here.

330
00:26:43.120 --> 00:26:45.640
Dear audience. in a few minutes
a siren will sound

331
00:26:45.880 --> 00:26:49.640
and after it the Memorial Day ceremony
for Israel's fallen will begin.

332
00:27:21.440 --> 00:27:24.080
Dana. they're here. I identify two
who were with me at the camp.

333
00:27:29.600 --> 00:27:33.960
Steve. advance to your one o'clock.
There are two suspects near the flower stand.

334
00:27:35.280 --> 00:27:36.320
Visual contact.

335
00:27:36.520 --> 00:27:38.840
Doron. is this a positive ID?
-A hundred percent.

336
00:27:40.400 --> 00:27:41.560
They'll wait for the siren.

337
00:27:43.680 --> 00:27:45.360
Dana. we should act now.

338
00:27:51.400 --> 00:27:53.480
I don't have a clean line of fire.
They're surrounded by civilians.

339
00:27:53.960 --> 00:27:56.480
Steve. Doron.
close in on them as much as possible.

340
00:27:56.720 --> 00:27:58.920
and stay alert. Looks like there are more.

341
00:28:57.840 --> 00:28:58.920
Everyone get down!

342
00:29:08.360 --> 00:29:09.360
Run. run. run!

343
00:29:09.680 --> 00:29:12.560
They're inside the compound. Open
the gates. evacuate civilians.

344
00:29:12.640 --> 00:29:14.360
This is Segev. Holon.
We have terrorists inside the crowd.

345
00:29:14.440 --> 00:29:17.440
This is Tzofar. There's gunfire. -This is 730.
We're extracting. Get to the compound.

346
00:29:17.600 --> 00:29:20.920
Dana. Danino and I are in pursuit of
one of them. He's heading downward.

347
00:29:22.960 --> 00:29:24.200
Move. move. move.
Steve. here he is!

348
00:29:33.400 --> 00:29:35.720
Move. move. move. move.
move. move. move! Move!

349
00:29:35.800 --> 00:29:37.640
Come here. Dana. Come here.
-Doron.

350
00:29:41.640 --> 00:29:42.520
Cover me.

351
00:29:43.720 --> 00:29:44.720
I'm reloading.

352
00:29:47.440 --> 00:29:48.600
Left. on the left.

353
00:29:49.960 --> 00:29:51.160
Two on the right.

354
00:30:00.960 --> 00:30:02.600
They're coming from the gate.
I'll try to stop them.

355
00:30:04.400 --> 00:30:05.320
Cover me.

356
00:30:35.760 --> 00:30:38.600
We need more people at the main gate.
They keep coming.

357
00:30:51.200 --> 00:30:53.200
Stay there! Everyone get down!

358
00:30:54.240 --> 00:30:56.440
Dana. stop them there. It's a trap.

359
00:30:57.600 --> 00:31:01.560
Run to the entrance. -Clear the people out!
Nobody run here!

360
00:31:04.080 --> 00:31:06.400
Nobody run here!
They're shooting! -Doron.

361
00:31:06.800 --> 00:31:08.600
Guys. -Move. move. move.

362
00:31:11.880 --> 00:31:13.720
Are you okay? Come. come.

363
00:31:32.360 --> 00:31:33.240
Said!

364
00:31:36.160 --> 00:31:37.120
Said!

365
00:31:38.360 --> 00:31:39.160
Stop!

366
00:31:44.440 --> 00:31:45.400
Stop!

367
00:31:52.120 --> 00:31:53.080
It's Khatib.

368
00:31:54.160 --> 00:31:55.080
Come. come this way.

369
00:32:05.160 --> 00:32:06.040
Said!

370
00:32:10.240 --> 00:32:11.200
Said.

371
00:32:34.080 --> 00:32:35.000
Amir.

372
00:32:39.160 --> 00:32:41.800
This is for Ali and his family.

373
00:32:42.240 --> 00:32:43.240
What is this? What is he doing?

374
00:32:45.560 --> 00:32:47.360
This is for October 7th.

375
00:32:55.200 --> 00:32:56.600
This is blood revenge.

376
00:33:01.080 --> 00:33:02.480
In Holon the area is clear.

377
00:33:02.680 --> 00:33:05.000
Seven civilians wounded.
five terrorists neutralized.

378
00:33:05.120 --> 00:33:07.440
In Hadera four terrorists neutralized.
We have ten dead.

379
00:33:07.520 --> 00:33:10.960
This is Kfar Saba. The incident is over.
Six terrorists neutralized.

380
00:33:11.080 --> 00:33:12.440
Conducting further sweeps.

381
00:33:17.520 --> 00:33:18.440
Dana.

382
00:33:20.640 --> 00:33:21.640
Dana. do you hear?

383
00:33:22.640 --> 00:33:24.080
Dana. give me an urgent report.

384
00:33:25.400 --> 00:33:27.800
The incident is over. There are casualties.

385
00:33:28.720 --> 00:33:30.480
About 15 terrorists neutralized.

386
00:34:06.040 --> 00:34:07.440
I'm too old for this.

387
00:34:44.200 --> 00:34:45.120
May I?

388
00:34:50.800 --> 00:34:52.240
How are you?

389
00:34:52.400 --> 00:34:53.920
Fine. I suppose.

390
00:34:54.040 --> 00:34:55.720
I just want to go home.

391
00:34:56.880 --> 00:34:58.640
Did you want to talk about something?

392
00:34:59.800 --> 00:35:01.800
I just wanted to check if you're okay.

393
00:35:02.400 --> 00:35:04.440
And to say thank you.

394
00:35:05.920 --> 00:35:07.200
For what?

395
00:35:09.560 --> 00:35:11.560
For making the right decision.

396
00:35:12.360 --> 00:35:13.760
You saved a lot of people.

397
00:35:14.680 --> 00:35:16.360
Including mine.

398
00:35:19.680 --> 00:35:20.880
You're welcome.

399
00:35:26.040 --> 00:35:28.480
Can I ask something?
Can you answer honestly?

400
00:35:28.920 --> 00:35:31.520
Yes. I'll try.

401
00:35:37.040 --> 00:35:39.160
Are you the one who killed Maher?

402
00:35:46.760 --> 00:35:47.840
I knew it.

403
00:35:53.640 --> 00:35:56.040
So that's the reason you were nice to me.

404
00:35:56.120 --> 00:35:58.240
you offered me a way out because you felt...

405
00:35:59.080 --> 00:36:02.640
guilty. -Guilty? No.
-No?

406
00:36:03.280 --> 00:36:04.520
So why?

407
00:36:05.640 --> 00:36:07.440
I felt sorry for you.

408
00:36:08.680 --> 00:36:11.440
You seem like a good person
who just lost her way.

409
00:36:12.200 --> 00:36:14.960
and I know how hard it is.
the death of family members.

410
00:36:17.520 --> 00:36:19.360
It can make you do
crazy things.

411
00:36:20.920 --> 00:36:24.080
Murder. revenge. things like that?

412
00:36:26.080 --> 00:36:28.520
So it seems I should feel sorry for you.

413
00:36:29.120 --> 00:36:31.440
Because you're still inside it
and you don't even realize.

414
00:36:32.000 --> 00:36:33.920
It's not the same thing.
-It is.

415
00:36:36.280 --> 00:36:40.520
When I was in the car.
I didn't press the button only because of...

416
00:36:41.280 --> 00:36:44.800
a little girl. Next to us. She...

417
00:36:45.920 --> 00:36:49.560
looked at me. and I told you at the camp.

418
00:36:49.680 --> 00:36:51.960
my only fear is doing something
I can't justify.

419
00:36:52.040 --> 00:36:56.400
and innocents shouldn't have to pay
for our sins. do you agree?

420
00:36:56.480 --> 00:36:57.440
Yes.

421
00:36:59.240 --> 00:37:03.640
So if you're grateful
for my decisions. like you said.

422
00:37:04.200 --> 00:37:05.720
can you stop?

423
00:37:10.400 --> 00:37:11.960
I'll do my best.

424
00:37:13.520 --> 00:37:14.880
I hope so.

425
00:37:15.880 --> 00:37:17.760
Ma'am. we have to go back.

426
00:37:29.040 --> 00:37:35.240
<i>"O God. full of mercy.</i>

427
00:37:35.680 --> 00:37:39.480
<i>who dwells on high.</i>

428
00:37:39.920 --> 00:37:44.400
<i>grant proper rest</i>

429
00:37:44.720 --> 00:37:47.200
<i>on the wings of the Divine Presence.</i>

430
00:37:47.400 --> 00:37:51.800
<i>in the heights of the holy and the pure.</i>

431
00:37:52.160 --> 00:37:54.400
<i>shining like the radiance of the sky.</i>

432
00:37:54.520 --> 00:37:58.680
<i>to the soul of</i>

433
00:37:58.920 --> 00:38:04.080
<i>Eliyahu son of Shalom and Geula.</i>

434
00:38:04.320 --> 00:38:06.520
<i>who has gone to his eternal rest.</i>

435
00:38:06.960 --> 00:38:13.920
<i>On behalf of Eliyahu son of Shalom and Geula.</i>

436
00:38:14.160 --> 00:38:19.520
<i>charity was pledged for the memory of his soul.</i>

